for web pages tool, and an efficient layout, this tool lets designers, deve=
lopers, and regular users easily capture color codes.=20

That is, in addition to color, many design elements and customizable websit=
es use HEX and RGB color codes =E2=80=93 simply hover over the color and co=
py or use it at any time. Obtain easy and precise color selection for all w=
eb elements using this online color picker tool.=20

=20

Key Features=20

Advanced Eyedropper Tool: How can one grab colors from websites so easily? =
This eyedropper for web pages allows users to capture colors from any pixel=
 on a webpage with ease.=20

HEX and RGB Support: Preview and transfer the color to your project in HEX =
and RGB color codes, making it suitable for different types of projects.=20

Color History: Go back to the color palette you recently chose with the col=
or history feature for easy access.=20

User-Friendly Interface: Clean design that lets you select color and copy t=
he color code identifier in just three clicks.=20

Enhanced Color Palette: For more color choices beyond the webpage elements,=
 use the integrated palette of this advanced color picker for designers.=20



How to Use the Color Picker Extension=20

Click the link from the Chrome Web Store to install the extension.=20

Open a Webpage: The colors can be captured from any webpage whenever the us=
er wants with the HEX color code picker.=20

Enable the Color Picker: By clicking on the extension icon, the eyedropper =
tool will launch.=20

Pick a Color: Power Tip: To capture the color of any element, move the mous=
e cursor over the screen and right-click: you'll see the RGB color grabber =
and HEX and RGB color codes formats.=20

Copy the Code: Instantly copy the color code and paste it wherever you need=
 it.=20

=20

FAQs=20

1. Can I see the color codes in both HEX and RGB?=20

Yes, the Color Picker provides both HEX and RGB formats for each color.=20

2. Is there a history feature to view recently selected colors?=20

Yes, the extension keeps a history of your recently picked colors for easy =
access.=20

